 <refsect1><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
 <para>
   Beatbox2 is really just a vehicle for me to make my music.
   But it is released in the hopes that it will be generally useful.
 </para>
 </refsect1>

 <refsect1><title>FORMAT OF A SCRIPT</title>
 <para>
   The overall format of a script is that it is a bunch of sections,
   each beginning with a line that begins with an equal sign.
   Here is a simple script:
   <programlisting><![CDATA[
=beats 100 90
=instrument drum modulate<exp-decay, sin>
=part instrument drum
acacaca
]]></programlisting>
   this script has three sections.  The first is the "beats" section
   which tells the number of beats and BPM of those beats.
   The second is the "instrument" section which defines the
   instrument "drum" as an exponential decay enveloping a sine wave.
   The third is a musical part, played on the aforementioned drum instrument,
   consisting of seven notes.
 </para>
